@AmandaT
"seeders" are people who have already downloaded the file. "leaches" are people who are trying to download the file. you are a "leach". without "seeds" your file wont download. the more "seeds" / less "leaches" a file has, the faster it will download. the only way to get more "seeders" is for people who have already finished downloading, to "seed" it.
